\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces $\lambda $ sweep comparing AmbGCE{} and TanGCE{} at matched step sizes across three concept domains (Qwen2.5-0.5B, layer~8). NL: retrained nonlinear probe accuracy on the target concept (lower = stronger erasure). AmbGCE{} deteriorates at high $\lambda $ (rising leakage), while TanGCE{} continues improving, supporting the claim that on-manifold updates can safely employ larger erasure strengths. Bold: best NL per domain.}}{9}{table.caption.27}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:lambda_sweep}{{3}{9}{$\lambda $ sweep comparing \AmbGCE {} and \TanGCE {} at matched step sizes across three concept domains (Qwen2.5-0.5B, layer~8). NL: retrained nonlinear probe accuracy on the target concept (lower = stronger erasure). \AmbGCE {} deteriorates at high $\lambda $ (rising leakage), while \TanGCE {} continues improving, supporting the claim that on-manifold updates can safely employ larger erasure strengths. Bold: best NL per domain}{table.caption.27}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces CLIP ViT-B/32 concept erasure on CelebA (validation HPO for $\lambda $). Each method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from the same grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy, ensuring a fair comparison. L/NL Leak: retrained linear / nonlinear probe accuracy on test (lower = better). $\Delta $Ctrl: mean control-task accuracy change across 5 least-correlated attributes (closer to zero = more surgical). Representation: CLIP ViT-B/32 pooled embedding (768 dimensions).}}{9}{table.caption.28}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:celeba_clip_fair}{{4}{9}{CLIP ViT-B/32 concept erasure on CelebA (validation HPO for $\lambda $). Each method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from the same grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy, ensuring a fair comparison. L/NL Leak: retrained linear / nonlinear probe accuracy on test (lower = better). $\Delta $Ctrl: mean control-task accuracy change across 5 least-correlated attributes (closer to zero = more surgical). Representation: CLIP ViT-B/32 pooled embedding (768 dimensions)}{table.caption.28}{}}
